The features, aspects and advantages of the semiconductor memory device according to the present invention will be more clearly understood from the following description taken in conjunction with the accompanying drawings in which:


FIG. 1A shows a cross-sectional view of a prior art MINT cell depicting the upper region of a trench, and wherein a doped polysilicon deposition is placed within a collar surrounding the outer surface of the trench;


FIG. 1B shows a prior art trench and partial polysilicon fill after formation of the isolation collar;


FIG. 2 shows a prior art fill in the upper region of the trench recessed below the pad dielectric and the isolation collar removed from the top region of the trench;


FIG. 3 shows a cross-sectional view of the polysilicon recessed below the depth of the isolation collar, in accordance with the invention;


FIG. 4 shows the n-epitaxial silicon in the strap region after planarization and recess to the level of the substrate;


FIG. 5 shows the trench capacitor and depletion-strap device after formation of the shallow trench isolation (STI);


FIG. 6 shows the device in the on-state with the majority carriers accumulated in the strap region under the gate; and


FIG. 7 shows the device shown in FIG. 6 in the off-state.
